import re

def parse_html(html):
    pattern = ''
    matches = re.findall(pattern, html)
    parsed_tags = []
    for match in matches:
        tag_attributes = match[0]
        tag_content = match[1]
        tag_content = re.sub('<.*?>', '', tag_content)
        parsed_tag = {'attributes': tag_attributes, 'content': tag_content}
        parsed_tags.append(parsed_tag)
    return parsed_tags
